<item>
            <title>[LU-6956] multiple test failures on el6.7</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6956</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have now seen the exact same test fails repeat on more than a singe test run on el6.7 client/server.  similar fails aren&apos;t seen in similar runs on el6.6.  This suggests that the root cause is in the kernel update, but I can&apos;t see it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/0f3acfdc-3a25-11e5-8f15-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/0f3acfdc-3a25-11e5-8f15-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/8d2ae154-3ae1-11e5-9384-5254006e85c2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/8d2ae154-3ae1-11e5-9384-5254006e85c2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;failed tests include&lt;br/&gt;
sanity: 77i, 120a, 127a, 133c, 151, 154f, 156, 224c&lt;br/&gt;
sanity-sec: 7-24 all Error: &apos;adding fops nodemaps failed 1&apos; &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
